  "prompt": "When Indian restaurant menus say \"green chili\", is there a particular type of chili pepper they usually mean?",
  "response": "In Indian cuisine, when menus refer to \"green chili,\" they typically mean a variety of small, slender, and often quite hot chili peppers that are commonly used in Indian cooking. The specific type can vary, but it often includes chilies like the Indian Jwala chili or similar varieties. These green chilies are used to add heat and a distinct flavor to numerous dishes. While the exact variety may differ depending on the region or the restaurant, they are generally fresh, green, and have a strong heat profile.",
